{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of trust by embezzling $25,000 from their employer. However, taking into account the lack of a prior criminal record and the effort made to partially restitute the stolen funds, a lengthy prison sentence is not mathematically or rehabilitatively warranted. A period of 6 months of actual incarceration is appropriate to serve as a deterrent and punishment for the abuse of fiduciary duty. This will be paired with probation and a mandate to complete the remaining restitution.",
  "verdict": 6
}
